did.abstract: This collection contains correspondence, postcards, handwritten/typed manuscripts, photographs, pre-publication proofs, art, and flyers. This material dates from 1984-2009 with the majority of the material falling within the dates 1988-2006. Most of the material consists of items mailed or sent to Buck Downs from other artists, poets, publisher, authors, and friends. Most of the material (whether typed manuscripts or graphic art) includes original poetry. This collection also contains some Buck Downs poems and professional papers.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: This Collection is organized into two series: Correspondence to Buck Downs and Poems and other paper.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content note
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, poems, postcards, handwritten/typed manuscripts, photographs, pre-publication proofs, slides, VHS/audio tapes, folk art (including paintings, papier-mâché, photographs, and collages), flyers, and article clippings. This material dates from 1984-2009 with the majority of the material falling within the dates 1988-2006. This collection consists of material gathered and/or created by Buck Downs. Most of the material consists of items mailed or sent to Buck Downs from other artists, poets, publisher, authors, and friends. Most of the material (whether typed manuscripts or graphic art) includes original poetry. Some of the material was sent to Buck Downs in consideration for publication. There is a large amount of material from Brett Evans. There are fair to substantial amounts of material from Jules Boykoff, Jeff Conant, CA Conrad, Jessica Freeman, Greg Fuchs, Heather Fuller, John McNally, Joe Ross, Rod Smith, and Ficus Strangulensis. This collection also contains Buck Down poems and professional papers (mostly in series two). The collection was donated by Buck Downs in 2009.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Buck Downs (1964-) is a poet, publisher, and editor who has been a long-time resident of Washington, D.C. Bucks Jordan Downs was born in Jones County, Mississippi on 07/28/1964. His parents are Jordon Downs and Fronia Gail Ulmer Downs. Buck Downs resides and works in Washington, D.C. Some of his poems have appeared in journals including Puppyflowers, Brooklyn Rail, and Columbia Poetry Review. His books include Ladies Love Outlaws, In Memory of D. Thompson, Small Pieces Loosely Joined, twist riffs & stiff hits, Recreational Vehicle, and Marijuana Softdrink. He is renowned for his high energy reading style. His CD Pontiac Fever was released by Narrow House Recordings in 2006. Buck is editor of Open 24 Hours and was formerly editor of other publications.

Part of this collection reflects his postcard project: "The postcard project began to find its current shape in 1993. I had been hand-typing individual poem-postcards, mailing them to poetry/art friends like Brett Evans, while concurrently doing the small-poet thing of compiling, mailing, and tracking responses to manuscripts from mostly presses and zines. The latter enterprise was depressing and unproductive, even when successful, while the poem-postcards turned out to be a positive hoot. So in the summer of 1993 I gave up the habit of sending work to magazine editors, and raided my address book to build a list of people whose opinions mattered to me. Since sometime in late 1993, I have kept a mailing list and sent out a monthly poem on a post card. The list has grown from a handful of friends to a couple hundred people" (Buck Downs, Dec. 2007).

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: The Correspondence to Buck Downs series is arranged alphabetically by last names, which is how the collection was organized when donated. Folders are labeled by full name. Some individuals have multiple folders containing their correspondence. Materials are not arranged within folders. There are also miscellaneous files labeled by first letter of last names (ex. Misc. H or Misc. P) for cases where there were few items from an individual.

This series consists of material gathered and/or created by Buck Downs, particularly some of his poems and professional papers.
